# bin/.scrub-extra-patterns  (DEFAULT, tracked — ships with the repo)
#
# scrub-check.sh loads this file at runtime and scans for every regex below
# alongside its built-in patterns. This DEFAULT carries only GENERIC patterns
# (no real account IDs, no personal names) so the public working tree stays
# clean by default.
#
# Operator-specific EXACT values (your real AWS account ID, private hostnames,
# private Slack channels) do NOT belong here — they would leak into the public
# repo. Put those in a private, gitignored override instead:
#
#     cp bin/.scrub-extra-patterns.example bin/.scrub-extra-patterns.local
#     ALFRED_SCRUB_EXTRA_PATTERNS=bin/.scrub-extra-patterns.local bash bin/scrub-check.sh
#
# bin/.scrub-extra-patterns.local is gitignored (see .gitignore). Pointing
# ALFRED_SCRUB_EXTRA_PATTERNS at it replaces this default; source both if you
# want both by concatenating them into one file.
#
# Format: one POSIX extended-regex per line. Blank lines and "# " comments
# ignored; a bare "#word" line is treated as a pattern, not a comment.

# (i) Bare operator home-directory paths. The built-in patterns already catch
# the .alfred / .hermes / Claude_Workspace layouts; broaden coverage to any
# dotfile dir that tends to carry host-private config (credentials, keys).
/Users/[A-Za-z0-9._-]+/\.(alfred|hermes|aws|ssh|config|gnupg|kube|docker)
/home/[A-Za-z0-9._-]+/\.(alfred|hermes|aws|ssh|config|gnupg|kube|docker)

# (ii) Bare 12-digit AWS account ID. Generic: any standalone 12-digit run.
# This is an identifier, not a secret, but it should not appear in a public
# repo. (bin/.scrub-extra-patterns.example is per-line-allowlisted so its
# documented placeholder does not trip this.)
\b[0-9]{12}\b
